{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"protocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","title":"MLNOverlay","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"},{"kind":"text","text":" <"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(pl)MLNAnnotation","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","text":"MLNAnnotation"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You use overlays to layer more sophisticated content on top of a map view. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use an overlay to show the boundaries of a national park or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trace a bus route along city streets. This SDK defines several concrete classes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that conform to this protocol and define standard shapes."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"],"title":"Inherits From"},{"type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"],"title":"Conforming Types"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/coordinate","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/intersectsOverlayBounds:"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","title":"MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"title":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/coordinate":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/coordinate","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/coordinate","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A coordinate representing the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"title":"coordinate","fragments":[{"text":"coordinate","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"title":"overlayBounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/intersectsOverlayBounds:":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a Boolean indicating whether the specified rectangle intersects the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"receiver’s shape."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/intersectsOverlayBounds:","title":"intersectsOverlayBounds:","fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"- "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"intersectsOverlayBounds:"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/intersectsoverlaybounds:","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"intersectsOverlayBounds:"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","title":"MLNPolygon","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"vertices, specified as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"text":" instances, and the edges that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolyline"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MLNMultiPolyline"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointCollection":{"title":"MLNPointCollection","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointCollection","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointcollection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disconnected vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"points in the collection may be related but are not connected spatially. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use a point collection to represent all the trees in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"orchard."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolygon":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolygon","title":"MLNMultiPolygon","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNMultiPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polygons that do not overlap. For example, you could use a multipolygon shape","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to represent the body of land that consists of an island surrounded by an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"atoll: the inner island would be one ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object, while the surrounding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"atoll would be another. You could also use a multipolygon shape to represent a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group of disconnected but related buildings.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolyline":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNPolyline","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of two or more vertices,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the line segments that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"path along which something moves."}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolyline","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolyline"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","title":"MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}]}}}